    <h2>Archival Materials</h2>
    <div class="fltrt-block">
    <div class="photoborder">
      <img src="/resources/images/1940s-Bowlers-at-City-Recreation-Lanes.jpg" alt="1940's Bowlers" title="1940's Bowlers" width="400" height="276"/>
    </div></div>
    <p>Over the years a number of archival  materials have been donated to the Sports Hall of Fame by the public. These  materials are used by staff, volunteers and the public for various research  projects on the history of sport. Included amongst the Hall of Fame archival collection are such things as  programs, scrapbooks and photographs.</p>
    <p>Access to the archival collection is  available by appointment. Reproductions  of archival materials are also available for a fee. For further information contact the Hall of  Fame by <a href="/aboutus/contact.aspx">clicking here.</a></p>
    <p>In addition to archival materials, the  Sports Hall of Fame also has an extensive collection of newspaper clippings on  individuals and sporting activities from across the region. Also available is a library featuring books  on local and general sports history.</p>

